  "texts": [
    "For Chinese, for example, this could be by character properties (number of strokes or radical), pronunciation-based, or respelling-based.",
    "Going back to alphabetic languages, signposts in the form of words appeared as headings of dictionary entries, acting as gateways to the detailed information contained within a dictionary, serving as entry headwords.",
    "To simplify vertical scanning, these headwords were often typographically emphasized with bold formatting and/ or hanging indentation.",
    "This whole arrangement followed a conventional system supposedly understood by dictionary users, although user studies launched in the late 20 th century (e.g.",
    "Atkins, 1998) revealed this assumption to be overly optimistic."
  ],
